President Omar el-Bashir of Sudan condemned the U.S. missile strikes on a pharmaceutical factory, denying allegations of chemical weapons production.
The Arab League and Arab states criticized the attacks as a breach of international law.
El-Bashir called for an American verification committee to inspect the factory.
Despite skepticism, he insisted the plant only produced medicines.
Diplomats from various nations expressed concern over the strikes, with Sudan planning to bring the issue to the UN Security Council.
The situation remains tense as Sudan asserts its right to self-defense.
